==Society and culture==

===Sales===
Gabapentin is best known under the brand name Neurontin manufactured by [[Pfizer]] subsidiary [[Parke-Davis]]. A Pfizer subsidiary named Greenstone markets generic gabapentin.

In December 2004 the FDA granted final approval to a generic equivalent to Neurontin made by the Israeli firm [[Teva Pharmaceutical Industries|Teva]].

Neurontin is one of Pfizer's best-selling drugs, and was one of the 50 most-prescribed [[Medication|drugs]] in the [[United States]] in 2003. However, Pfizer has come under heavy criticism and serious litigation for its marketing of Neurontin. They face allagations that, behind the scenes, [[Parke-Davis]] marketed the drug for at least a dozen supposed uses that the [[David Franklin (scientist)|FDA]] had not approved.<ref name="pmid16908923">
